'''第13769号行政命令'''（{{lang-en|Executive Order 13769}}），[[美國聯邦政府|美國聯邦政府]][[联邦公报|公报]]官方名称为《阻止外国恐怖分子进入美国的国家保护计划》（{{lang|en|Protecting the Nation from Foreign Terrorist Entry into the United States}}）<ref>{{cite news|author1=梅尔顿|title=川普签署禁止叙利亚难民进入美国的法令|url=http://www.voachinese.com/a/trump-executive-order-/3696465.html|accessdate=2017-01-29|agency=[[美國之音|美國之音]]|date=2017-01-28|archive-date=2017-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129121843/http://www.voachinese.com/a/trump-executive-order-/3696465.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，是[[美國|美國]][[美國總統|總統]][[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]在2017年1月27日簽署並即刻生效的[[行政命令_(美国)|行政命令]]。該法令旨在禁止7個位於[[中東|中東]]及[[非洲|非洲]]、且为[[穆斯林世界|穆斯林居多的國家]]的人民入境美國，对擁有[[美國簽證|美國簽證]]或[[綠卡|綠卡]]身分者也有效（已被豁免）<ref name="BBC key">{{cite web |title=Trump's refugee and travel suspension: Key points |website=BBC News |date=2017-01-28 |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38781302 |accessdate=2017-01-29 |archive-date=2019-05-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507032822/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38781302 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WSJ">{{cite web |last=Nicholas |first=Peter |last2=Nicholas |first2=Peter |title=White House Defends Executive Order Barring Travelers From Certain Muslim Countries |website=WSJ |date=2017-01-28 |url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/white-house-defends-executive-order-barring-travelers-from-certain-muslim-countries-1485642323 |accessdate=2017-01-29 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308160302/https://www.wsj.com/articles/white-house-defends-executive-order-barring-travelers-from-certain-muslim-countries-1485642323 |dead-url=no }}</ref>；同時暫停{{le|难民接纳项目|United States Refugee Admissions Program}}（{{lang-en|United States Refugee Admissions Program}}）120天，以及90天內禁止來自[[利比亞|利比亞]]、[[伊朗|伊朗]]、[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]、[[索馬里|索馬里]]、[[蘇丹|蘇丹]]、[[敘利亞|敘利亞]]和[[也門|也門]]等7國國民入境美國，其中敘利亞的期限為「無限期」<ref>{{cite web|author1=THE WHITE HOUSE|title=PROTECTING the Nation from Foreign Terrorist Entry into the United States|url=https://ir.usembassy.gov/protecting-nation-foreign-terrorist-entry-united-states/|accessdate=2017-01-29|archive-date=2017-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128210754/https://ir.usembassy.gov/protecting-nation-foreign-terrorist-entry-united-states/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

行政命令发出后立刻受到[[民主党_(美國)|民主党]]的強烈反对。有大量示威者到各机场抗议该行政命令的[[示威|示威]]，並作出[[法律行动|法律行动]]。2017年2月3日，在[[华盛顿州诉特朗普|华盛顿州诉特朗普]]一案中，一个全国范围的[[禁制令|临时禁制令]]暂停了该行政命令的大部分执行。在联邦政府上诉后，该裁决于2017年2月9日再次被[[美国第九巡回上诉法院|美国第九巡回上诉法院]]维持。

特朗普于2018年3月6日签署了[[第13780号行政命令|第13780号行政命令]]来取代该本行政命令，之后还颁布了第9645号总统公告（Presidential Proclamation 9645）增订一些附加信息。这一系列有关旅行的禁令被统称为“[[特朗普旅行禁令|特朗普旅行禁令]]”。

2018年6月26日，[[美国最高法院|最高法院]]以5-4作出支持第13780号行政命令和第9645号总统公告{{link-en|特朗普诉夏威夷州案|Trump v. Hawaii|裁定}}，并由[[美国首席大法官|首席大法官]][[约翰·罗伯茨|约翰·罗伯茨]]起草了多数意见书。<ref>{{cite news|title=Trump’s Travel Ban Is Upheld by Supreme Court|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/26/us/politics/supreme-court-trump-travel-ban.html|publisher=nytimes.com|work=Adam Liptak and Michael D. Shear|date=2018-06-26|accessdate=2018-06-26|archive-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626151640/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/26/us/politics/supreme-court-trump-travel-ban.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

美国总统[[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]于就任首日签署行政命令，废除了特朗普的第13780号行政命令以及第9645号总统公告。<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/presidential-actions/2021/01/20/proclamation-ending-discrimina y-bans-on-entry-to-the-united-states/ | title = Proclamation on Ending Discriminatory Bans on Entry to The United States | work = White House | date =2021-01-20 | accessdate =2021-01-27}}</ref>

==背景==
美国于2015年制定的免签证计划（Visa Waiver Program Improvement）和防止恐怖分子入境法案（Terrorist Travel Prevention Act），作为美国1.1万亿美元[[支出法案|支出法案]]的一部分，已由前总统[[巴拉克·奥巴马|巴拉克·奥巴马]]签署成为了[[法律|法律]]。<ref name=Visas2016>[https://travel.state.gov/content/visas/en/law-and-policy/statistics/annual-reports/report-of-the-visa-office-2016.html Report of the Visa Office 2016] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204021432/https://travel.state.gov/content/visas/en/law-and-policy/statistics/annual-reports/report-of-the-visa-office-2016.html |date=2017-02-04 }}. Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State.</ref>而在这项法案中，[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]、[[伊朗|伊朗]]、[[苏丹|苏丹]]和[[叙利亚|叙利亚]]这四个国家被标为需要签证才可赴美的国家。并且在2016年，[[利比亚|利比亚]]、[[索马里|索马里]]和[[也门|也门]]这三个国家也被追加列入其中。然而有评论指出，这个国家名单其实较具随意性，如[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]（因新闻报道该国与恐怖组织有来往<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/features/2017/01/23/Why-does-ISIS-use-suicide-belts-in-Saudi-Arabia-.html |title=Why is ISIS obsessed over use of suicide belts in Saudi Arabia? |access-date=2017-01-31 |archive-date=2019-09-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916100849/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/features/2017/01/23/Why-does-ISIS-use-suicide-belts-in-Saudi-Arabia-.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>）就没有在这个列表之中。<ref>{{cite web |title=U.S. Expands Visa Waiver Restrictions For Recent Travelers To Libya, Somalia, Yemen |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/visa-waiver-libya-somalia-yemen_us_56c5fc45e4b0c3c550540558 |website=The Huffington Post |accessdate=January 30, 2017 |archive-date=2018-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181221205831/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/visa-waiver-libya-somalia-yemen_us_56c5fc45e4b0c3c550540558 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/114th-congress/house-bill/158 |title=H.R.158 - 114th Congress (2015-2016): Visa Waiver Program Improvement and Terrorist Travel Prevention Act of 2015 |publisher=Congress.gov |accessdate=January 29, 2017 |archive-date=2019-03-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331100713/https://www.congress.gov/bill/114th-congress/house-bill/158 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/whats-the-real-deal-on-this-muslim-ban/article/2613279 |title=What's the real deal on this 'Muslim ban'? |work=Washington Examiner |accessdate=January 29, 2017 |archive-date=2017-11-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102135113/http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/whats-the-real-deal-on-this-muslim-ban/article/2613279 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]在美东时间2017年1月20日正式就任[[美国总统|美国总统]]。在此之前，特朗普一直秉持着一种观念，即世界上有许多[[伊斯蘭恐怖主義|極端伊斯蘭恐怖分子]]正在利用美国的[[难民|难民]]安置项目进入美国<ref name=thehill_lawsuit>{{cite web |url=http://thehill.com/policy/national-security/316676-legal-groups-file-lawsuit-against-trump-administration-amid-refugee |title=ACLU sues White House over immigration ban |first=Max |last=Greenwood |work=The Hill |date=January 28, 2017 |access-date=2017-01-31 |archive-date=2022-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220113141937/https://thehill.com/policy/national-security/316676-legal-groups-file-lawsuit-against-trump-administration-amid-refugee |dead-url=no }}</ref>。总部位于美国华盛顿的“移民政策机构”（Migration Policy Institute）2015年发表的报告显示，自2001年的[[9·11恐怖袭击事件|9·11恐怖袭击事件]]之后，有78.4万的难民已经在美国境内定居，但其中只有3名难民因为涉及暴恐被捕<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/sep/02/donald-trump-syria-refugees-us-immigration-security-terrorism|title=Trump and Syrian refugees in the US: separating the facts from fiction|last=Gambino|first=Lauren|date=2016-09-02|newspaper=The Guardian|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|access-date=2017-01-31|archive-date=2021-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210426065021/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/sep/02/donald-trump-syria-refugees-us-immigration-security-terrorism|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在总统初选活动中，在2015年12月7日加州發生恐怖襲擊後，特朗普提出要实行一种临时禁令，以限制[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]入境美国<ref name=thehill_lawsuit/><ref name=wp_background>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/01/28/mike-pence-once-called-trumps-muslim-ban-unconstitutional-he-just-applauded-the-order/ |script-title=en:Pence once called Trump's Muslim ban ‘unconstitutional.’ He now applauds a ban on refugees. |work=The Washington Post |accessdate=January 28, 2017 |archive-date=2021-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215013137/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/01/28/mike-pence-once-called-trumps-muslim-ban-unconstitutional-he-just-applauded-the-order/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=reuters_before>{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-immigration-exclusive-idUSKBN1582XQ |title=Trump expected to order temporary ban on refugees |date=January 25, 2017 |accessdate=January 28, 2017 |agency=Reuters |archive-date=2021-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210310012903/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-immigration-exclusive-idUSKBN1582XQ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而这一种提议因基於宗教信仰，而受到了美国政界普遍的反对。<ref name=wp_background/>[[迈克·彭斯|迈克·彭斯]]（现任美国副总统，也是特朗普的竞选搭档，時任[[印第安納州|印第安納州]]州長）也是这项政策的反对者之一，将特朗普的这一举措形容为“冒犯的”、“违宪的”<ref name=wp_background/>。而在[[2016年奥兰多夜店枪击案|2016年奥兰多夜店枪击案]]发生之后<ref>{{cite news |last=Beckiwth |first=Ryan Teague |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Read Donald Trump's Speech on the Orlando Shooting |url=http://time.com/4367120/orlando-shooting-donald-trump-transcript/ |work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=January 28, 2017 |archive-date=2021-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320141852/https://time.com/4367120/orlando-shooting-donald-trump-transcript/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，特朗普和司法部长候选人[[傑夫·塞申斯|傑夫·塞申斯]]则将他们的注意力转移了恐怖活动的地理区域，而非直截了当地指出某个宗教需要“被审查”（the method of vetting）。在美国参议院听证会上，民主黨联邦参议员[[廣野慶子|廣野慶子]]就移民问题对塞申斯提出询问，他表示了部分赞同：“（这项政策）也不失为一种可行的方法（去审查移民者身份），可以对恐怖分子活动频繁的高风险地区发挥作用。」<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sessions.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2016/6/at-least-580-individuals-convicted-in-terror-cases-since-9-11-at-least-380-are-foreign-born |title=AT LEAST 580 INDIVIDUALS CONVICTED IN TERROR CASES SINCE 9/11, AT LEAST 380 ARE FOREIGN-BORN |last=Sessions |first=Jeff |date=June 22, 2016 |website= |accessdate=January 28, 2017 |quote=When compared with [the Obama] Administration's immigration policies, and bearing in mind the four major terrorist attacks in the United States in the last year alone, this inability to properly screen individuals from abroad and assimilate those we admit paints a striking picture. Between Fiscal Years 2009 and 2014, the United States granted green cards to approximately 832,000 individuals from Muslim-majority countries… |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126063729/http://www.sessions.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2016/6/at-least-580-individuals-convicted-in-terror-cases-since-9-11-at-least-380-are-foreign-born |archivedate=2017年1月26日 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://time.com/4367120/orlando-shooting-donald-trump-transcript/ |title=Read Donald Trump's Speech on the Orlando Shooting |last=Trump |first=Donald |date=June 13, 2016 |work=Time |accessdate=January 29, 2017 |quote=Each year the United States permanently admits 100,000 immigrants from the Middle East and many more from Muslim countries outside of the Middle East. Our government has been admitting ever- growing numbers, year after year, without any effective plan for our own security. |archive-date=2021-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320141852/https://time.com/4367120/orlando-shooting-donald-trump-transcript/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> <ref>{{cite video |title=Attorney General Nominee Jeff Sessions Testifies at Confirmation Hearing |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?420932-101/attorney-general-nominee-jeff-sessions-testifies-confirmation-hearing&start=17545 |publisher=C-SPAN |time=54:19 |date=January 10, 2017 |accessdate=January 29, 2017 |archive-date=2019-08-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816180215/https://www.c-span.org/video/?420932-101%2Fattorney-general-nominee-jeff-sessions-testifies-confirmation-hearing&start=17545 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在之前，特朗普题为“与美国选民的约定”（Contract with the American Voter）的竞选演讲中，他支持对恐怖活动高发地区做出移民入境限制<ref>{{cite speech |title= Donald Trump's speech on fighting terrorism |first= Donald |last= Trump |location= Youngstown, OH |date= 15 August 2016 |url= http://www.politico.com/story/2016/08/donald-trump-terrorism-speech-227025 |access-date= 30 January 2017 |archive-date= 2021-02-05 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210205124755/https://www.politico.com/story/2016/08/donald-trump-terrorism-speech-227025 |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://assets.donaldjtrump.com/_landings/contract/O-TRU-102316-Contractv02.pdf |title=Donald Trump's Contract with the American Voter |last=Trump |first=Donald |date=October 23, 2016 |website=DonaldJTrump.com |access-date=January 30, 2017 |quote=my administration will immediately pursue the following…actions to restore security… suspend immigration from terror-prone regions where vetting cannot safely occur. |archive-date=2018-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180307133648/https://assets.donaldjtrump.com/_landings/contract/O-TRU-102316-Contractv02.pdf |dead-url=no }}.</ref>。如今，特朗普政府签署了这项行政命令，旨在践行竞选时发出的承诺。特朗普的竞选政见对所谓“恐怖活动高发地区”的理解，与[[参议院|参议院]]所谓对移民做出限制的这一声音是前呼后应的，这种状况在2012年就初现端倪。而特朗普的竞选官网则对塞申斯提出了赞扬，并指出其在移民政策中扮演着明智的建言者，这种表态最早是在2015年出现的。史蒂芬·米勒（Stephen Miller，美国政治竞选策划家，曾为特朗普的竞选服务）被《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》称为移民、签证禁令幕后的“总设计师”（Major Architect），米勒在成为特朗普的首席顾问及演讲稿撰写人之前，已经对[[参议员|参议员]]塞申斯对于移民政策的观点进行了了解。

